						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Slab lying in Hirēmaṭha.</hi></p>						

						<p>[A.D. 1609.]</p>						

						<p>The extant portion of the date of this damaged record is <hi rend="bold">Saumya, Pushya, śu. 13, Wednesday, Uttarāyaṇa-saṁkramaṇa.</hi> On palaeographical grounds the date may be probably equated with <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1609, December 27, Wednesday, f.d.t. ·66.</hi> The <hi rend="italic">saṁkramaṇa</hi> occurred on the next day.</p>						

						<p>The inscription registers a gift of oil for a lamp to a deity by some trade-guilds <hi rend="italic">(sameya)</hi> at <hi rend="bold">Kalkere.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
